page.title: 05Coxheath village
page.content: Coxheath is a medium sized village near Maidstone in Kent. It is surrounded by a number of farms, many growing apples and cherries. In the village centre there are a number of shops including a D.I.Y. store and a car showroom. There are also two Newsagents, one off-Licence,two Butchers, two take-away stores and one hair salon. There is also one Bank, one Church,two Pubs and one Spar store and a Chemist. This Shopping centre is situated around a crossroads. Surrounding the crossroads is a large residential area. The majority of houses are semi-detached,with a large proportion of detached houses and bungalows. There is only a small number of flats.
